subject: p15131736
Findings: The heart is moderately enlarged. There is a widespread interstitial abnormality with indistinct pulmonary vascularity and upper zone redistribution, most consistent with moderate pulmonary edema. There is no definite pleural effusion or pneumothorax.
Impression: Findings most consistent with moderate pulmonary edema.
